    "language": "es",
    "seed_source": "Same as gate-1-vocabulary.json (HiddenLayer APE, garak PromptInject + DAN). Surface forms hand-curated by reading all 50 injection rows in docs/issues/52-cowork-outputs/gate-1-corpus-es.jsonl and cross-referencing against gate-1-translations.json.",
    "design_note": "Spanish equivalents of the 16 English primitives in gate-1-vocabulary.json. Primitive ids and APE refs and definitions are copied verbatim from the English pack so cross-language metrics align. Only the `patterns` list is re-authored per language.",
    "applicability": "Spanish surface forms only. Tested against gate-1-corpus-es.jsonl (50 inj / 50 ben). Not cross-language. English loanwords are retained for jailbreak_persona because Google Translate (and most Spanish attackers) carry DAN/DUDE/STAN/JAILBREAK verbatim; see docs/issues/52-cowork-outputs/gate-1-corpus-es.jsonl holdout_injection_0059 / 0026 / 0054 / 0050 for examples.",
    "unicode_handling": "Patterns use ASCII-only word boundaries (\\b) because Spanish shares the Latin alphabet with English; no Han-character special casing required. Case-insensitive matching is applied by the runner (re.IGNORECASE).",
    "notes_on_retained_english_primitives": [
      "imperative_emphasis retains the [A-Z]{15,} all-caps rule — Spanish injections routinely shout in all caps (e.g. 'COMIENCE TODAS Y CADA UNA DE LAS SALIDA', 'CUALQUIER COSA').",
      "jailbreak_persona retains English loanwords DAN/DUDE/STAN/AIM/DevMode and adds Spanish glosses ('hacer cualquier cosa ahora', 'modo desarrollador').",
      "encoded_payload retains base64/rot13/hex as they appear verbatim even in Spanish text.",
      "policy_puppetry retains XML/JSON tags verbatim since attackers copy them literally."
    ]
  },
